5 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 15.1-19-03.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 15.1-19-03.1. Recitation of prayer - Period of silence - Pledge of allegiance.
8 1. A student may voluntarily pray aloud or participate in religious speech at any time
9 before, during, or after the schoolday to the same extent a student may voluntarily
10 speak or participate in secular speech.
11 2. A student of a public or nonpublic school may not be prohibited from voluntarily
12 participating in any student-initiated prayer at an activity held on the premises of a
13 public or nonpublic school.
14 3. A school board, school administrator, or teacher may not impose any restriction on the
15 time, place, manner, or location of any student-initiated religious speech or prayer
16 which exceeds the restriction imposed on students' secular speech.
17 4. A school board may, by resolution, allow a classroom teacher to impose up to one
18 minute of silence for meditation, reflection, or prayer at the beginning of each
19 schoolday.
20 5. A school board may authorize the voluntary recitation ofstudent of a public school shall
21 recite the pledge of allegiance by a teacher or one or more students at the beginning
22 of each schoolday. A student may not be required to recitemust be informed by written
23 notice published in the student handbook, or similar publication, that the student may
24 be excused from reciting the pledge of allegiance, stand during the recitation of the
25 pledge of allegiance, or salute the American flag upon written request by the student's
26 parent or legal guardian. During the pledge of allegiance, any unexcused student shall
27 show full respect to the flag by standing at attention with the right hand over the heart
28 and, for males, removing any headdress, except when the headdress is worn for
29 religious purposes.
